Public transport (MHD) will introduce the puzzle in their ticketing system on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, will be recorded in the history of the Pražský Dopravní Entrepreneurship (Pragus Transport Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will get into the subway, trams and buses, which instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, the latter is accessible for approximately 100 thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a coupon 30 days or 90 days (that will be valid from 1 January 2009) and both store it on their card in the information points and offices of the Dopravní Entrepreneur (the Transport Agency), located in the metro stations Lukaská hradrov Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží zaešovice, Kaśnyň, Rajčeň, Anděl
From yesterday, there is also the possibility of purchasing coupons online on the websites of the Dopravní enterprise: www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred people enjoyed the service during the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can definitively forget the guichets in the subway stations, where they had to be pitched with impatience in long curves in order to obtain paper tickets.
In fact, they will buy their coupon on the internet and will be stored on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these contact points, there is a guide with trained staff available to passengers, which will help those interested in purchasing the internet and will also register the coupon they bought on their card," said Martin Opatrný, spokesman of the project.
Beside the libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, reminding the composing machines of tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the metro stations Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be eighty," Opatrný added.
Automatic controls the coupon instead of the driver
Automatics that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Just enter the Opencard chip card and the previously purchased coupon will register itself on the card.
Electronic coupons are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital but also in the surroundings of the city.
I.e. in the periurban trains and bus lines 300 to 499, which are mainly used by residents of the Central Bohemian municipalities to access the capital.
